The Nigeria Customs Service (NCS), Federal Operations Unit (FOU) Zone B, on Friday in Kaduna said it has arrested and impounded illegal trailers loaded with donkey hides and skins worth over N320 million. Comptroller Federal Operations Unit (FOU), Zone B, A.B. Hamisu while briefing newsmen on Friday, said the items suspected to have been either smuggled or improperly imported into Nigeria through its land borders with total Duty Paid Value (DPV) of N320,305,521.78m were all seized in Kaduna. Hamisu explained that the seizures within the zone were done within a month, adding that other items seized include 1,214 bags of foreign imported rice worth N43,463,179, 21 units of vehicles worth N186,203,693, 14 means of conveyance worth N142,735,514 and seven units of used vehicles worth N43,468,179. He further added that other items seized are 157 bales of foreign second-hand clothing worth N23,451,286, a truckload of donkey hides and skin worth N20,797,041, 30 bundles of foreign new textile worth N9,698,714 and 114 kegs of vegetable oil (25 litres) worth N7,530,697. Similarly, duty was raised on 46 cartons of Tecno mobile phones worth N6,355,260, imported through Kano Airport, adding that 802 cartons of foreign spaghetti and macaroni worth N4,768,122, 800 sacks of adulterated motor oil worth N3,440,000, 89 sacks of foreign rice concealed in beans worth N3,214,947, 44 bags of foreign rice concealed in millet worth N1,589,412 and 30 cartons of foreign soap worth N1,505,250. He explained that his officers and men also intercepted 510 kegs of premium motor spirit (PMS) 25 litres worth N963,823.50, 110 pieces of foreign used tyres worth N801,317, 53 cartons of foreign matches worth N840,269, 38 cartons of foreign tinned tomato paste worth N1,405,730.20m. According to him, in view of the logistics required, some of the items could not be moved to the zonal headquarters in Kaduna.